content.description: Start on right of rail traverse left. Big reach up and left to good slot.  Then grab a big block to your left and move around corner into small alcove, then topout.
content.location: Starts on rail in middle of overhang. Down climb on left side or go back between boulders and around.

content.description: Good movement on small crimps, start sitting. For bonus, start on HfH, and finish on this line.
content.location: Far right side of the Habitat wall.

content.description: Lay start far left as per habitat for humanity. Traverse across the rail and up a "c" shaped hueco then top out to the right on a big knob. This route stops traversing before the small crimps on habitat for humanity but delivers a good pump. If you start on the rail the grade drops to v4.
content.location: Start far left on habitat for humanity.

content.description: Pull the overhang from the rail through good holds on right side just left of the "c" shaped hueco after the lip join topout to the right on a big knob.

Start in middle of big rail of Habitat for Humanity problem, work yourself out of the roof towards the left side of the right black streak. Use positive holds on left side of streak to top of streak, then cross to another jug on the right at top of streak and top out. Fun easy route on Habitat boulder.
content.location: Start in middle of huge rail under the roof of the habitat boulder. Obvious easiest problem on boulder.

content.description: Start all the way down in the back left of the cave on good holds.  After you get to the obvious large rail, proceed up to the lip on good holds.  The newish guidebook incorrectly labels this line as Habitat for Humanity- which continues traversing right to crimps before topping out.
content.location: Start is on the far left side of the cave, all the way back.  Finishes above the large rail on jugs.

content.description: Start close to the ground on the far left in the overhang on good holds, traverse right then outward on pockets to long rail. Traverse right on rail then through small alcove. Grab the bottom of the "c" shaped hueco. Use kneebar or power to move outside of overhang onto small crimps traversing right. Keep going right to edge of the boulder then up through better holds and decent topout.
content.location: Start is on the far left side of the overhang, finish is on the far right top of the boulder.
